metadata.name: Introspection
metadata.description:
In silence, with the modesty of a civilized animal that has lost its instinct, man distances himself from his habits and actions to immerse himself in the species and float on its foam like a wave. The fog mercilessly disintegrates him and invites him to pause for a moment in the journey and to analyze the meaning of his solitude. He ceases to be a simple sociable subject, mannered, false and inconsistent, and seeks the company of his own ideas. The fog, with its ancestral power of forcing synthesis and concentration, has the virtue of disturbing man and leading him along a path of unusual reflection.
